This paper focuses on the tradeoff between data utility and privacy risk in mobile phone metadata, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the value of data at various spatial and temporal granularity levels, which relates to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes a formal measure of reidentification risk, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the need for data-sharing models that provide adjustable degrees of accountability and security, which relates to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SD).
